name: Harding's
directions: Go past the bar and turn right through the doorway. The door is labeled "WC".

name: Dyanna Body & Nail Salon-Spa:Brazilian Waxing:Hair Removal:Electrolysis:New York‎
comment: You can pee before or after waxing.

name: the New School University
directions: Between Fifth and Sixth Avenues, on the 13th St. side. Ask guards (there may be 2 there) if you can use the restrooms. They are on the same floor (no need to use the elevator) Make a left then a right, then left. There are 2 gender neutral handicap accessible restrooms. You may need to be a student, but I've had luck entering (you don't have to be a student, just ask)
comment:
Enter through doors all the way to the right of the 3 doors.
Open 24/7.

name: Lion Brand Yarn Studio
directions: Next to cash register.
comment: LGBT friendly yarn shop.

name: Lion Brand Yarn Studio
directions: To the left of the cash register area.

name: Starbucks
directions: Right by Christopher Street stop on the 1 train. Not too far from West 4th street.

name: EN
directions: Through the front door, head to the right toward the bar and the bathroom hallway is on the left toward the end of the bar.
comment: Just walk right in, if questioned, say you're meeting a friend but they aren't there yet.

name: Henrietta Hudson
directions: Right on the other side of the room when you walk in through the door
comment: They are very nice and accepting of gender identities there, so you can tell them as much or as little as you want about why you're there

name: Stonewall Inn
directions: Has two bathrooms, intentionally gender neutral, one labeled 'All Gender,' one labeled 'Has Urinals.' Both are single occupancy.
comment: Stonewall Inn is a gay bar and National Monument. Iconic site of LGBT liberation. However, there is a reported case of sexual assault in the bathroom.

name: Madison Square Park
directions: This a paid public toilet.  It is located across from the historic MetLife clock tower in Madison Square park.  It is located on the corner of 23rd Street and Madison Ave.

name: Caffe Bene
directions: In the back, door code 5836.(subject to change)
comment: They don't really care if you have the door code already.

name: Argo tea cafe
directions: All the way to the right
comment: Must be a paying customer to get the code

name: Morandi
directions: On the left when you walk into the restaurant it says WC on the door, they’re all private “water closets”.

name: Bearburger
directions: All the way in the back on the right of the bar
comment: Two unisex, single-user restrooms.

name: Woodside Community Library
directions: On mezzanine level, accessible by stairs or elevator.  One public restroom, only one person at a time.  Get the key at the reference desk.  You will be prompted for a library card/some form of ID at the desk, for them to hold while you have the key.  This is because people steal the key.

name: Sotto 13
directions: straight in the second and third doors on the right after the bar.
comment: I work at this place, it's a restaurant so it's preferable that you're a paying customer but if it's not super busy (which it's usually not) we don't mind if you come in and ask if you can use the restroom (sometimes even if we're not open yet)

name: Sotto 13
directions: straight in the second and third doors on the right after the bar.
comment: I work at this place, it's a restaurant so it's preferable that you're a paying customer but if it's not super busy (which it's usually not) we don't mind if you come in and ask if you can use the restroom (sometimes even if we're not open yet)

name: Little Island Public Restroom
street: Little Island, Pier 55 at Hudson River Park Hudson River Greenway, New York, NY 10014
directions: Right after the little sitting area. If you're nearby Little Island you should be able to find it in Google Maps under public restroom.

name: 300 E 40th St #17E, New York, NY 10016, USA
directions: By the counter and all the way in the back.

name: LGBT Community Center (NYC)
directions: There are gender-specific and gender-neutral bathrooms here. You don't have to pay, just walk in. Ask the desk attendant what type of bathroom you want (All Gender, women, men ).

name: Spoon table & bar
directions: In the back behind the dining room

name: Paris baguette boulangerie
directions: Bakery on Lexington
comment: There are two bathrooms, both unisex

name: RAYMI Restaurant
directions: 1 gender neutral wheelchair accessible bathroom upstairs. 10 individual gender neutral single stalls downstairs.
comment: Upstairs and downstairs restrooms only available to restaurant patrons. Single stall downstairs bathrooms only open for dinner service starting at 5pm

name: The Spotted Pig
directions: Second floor by the stairs
comment: There are two stalls, but it is very cramped. The stalls are very small. But the restaurant is very LGBT+ Supportive as a whole, and the bathroom is unisex.

name: Starbucks
directions: Two gender neutral, single-stall, locking restrooms in an alcove across from the counter. Disabled persons should enter through the ramp in the main entrance of the building to avoid stairs.
comment: Must be a paying customer. As for the code at the front counter.

name: The Smith
directions: All the way at the end past the bar on the right-hand side tucked in a little hallway

name: Hillside Country BBQ
directions: They've got a bunch of gendered bathrooms downstairs, but they have one Unisex one on the main floor in the back past the BBQ pits, right across from the "employees only" door.
comment: I believe you have to be a paying customer, but I'm not certain.

name: Salvation Taco
directions: Down stairwell B

name: THINK COFFEE
directions: In the back

name: Think Coffee
directions: All the way in the back, on the right side.
comment: There are no signs stating that the restroom is for paying customers only; however this is probably the policy. With the LGBT center only a block away, I would advise going there if you weren't going to buy anything at Think.

name: Think Coffee
directions: All the way in the back, on the right side.
comment: There are no signs stating that the restroom is for paying customers only; however this is probably the policy. With the LGBT center only a block away, I would advise going there if you weren't going to buy anything at Think.

comment: Typically, the people at the reception desk will allow non-employees to use the restroom, but unfortunately it's not guaranteed.

name: Public restroom
street: S Loop Rd, W Loop Rd
directions: Right before the entrance to the four freedoms park

name: Congregation Beit Simchat Torah
directions: Go through the courtyard and up the ramp to 2nd floor entrance
comment: CBST is New York's LGBTQS synagogue serving people of all sexual orientations and gender identities

name: Starbucks
comment: Have to be paying customer but there's no key for the bathroom

name: LIM College - Maxwell Hall
directions: 8th floor, to the right of the elevators
comment: Must be a student/staff with a college ID

name: Chipotle
directions: Near the cash register
comment: You must have a receipt with a bathroom code

name: Argo Tea
directions: Straight past the seating area all the way on the right.
comment:
You really don't need to be a paying customer. As long as your not being loud or obnoxious, the staff probably won't notice. Maybe because it's a relatively lgbt-friendly area, or because some of the staff is lgbt, they're always really nice even if they do notice. But if you decide to buy something, a lot of the drinks are 2-3 dollars. 
Open daily from 6/7am - 11pm.

name: Argo tea
directions: Straight through past the seating areas to the far right.
comment:
You don't need to be a paying customer, if you present as clean and aren't being loud or obnoxious, the staff really won't mind. Maybe because it's a very lgbt friendly area, or because some of the staff is lgbt. Just go in and do whatchu need to do. And if you want to buy something, a lot of the drinks are 2-3 dollars. 
Open 6/7 am- 11 pm

name: Blue Agave
comment: In the back. For customers.

name: Argo tea cafe
directions: Halfway in on the right
comment: Must be a paying customer to get the code

name: BRGR
directions: Towards the back of the building. There are two unisex restrooms. One is labeled \\\"Vegetarian\\\" and the other is labeled \\\"Carnivore.\\\"

name: Cafe Gigi
directions: Straight in the back. One gender-neutral restroom available.

name: The Graduate Hotel
comment: No sinks in the stall but clean and spacious

name: Brooklyn Public Library/Bay Ridge Branch
directions: Single stall occupancy, one on each floor by the elevators.

name: The Whitney
directions: on "education" level there is an all gender restroom as well as gendered.
comment: unless you have a membership, you do have to pay to get in, but while you're there it's good to know about

comment: All gender bathroom in Whitney Museum of Art

name: 19 E 40th St, New York, NY 10016, USA

comment: You have to have admission to the museum. It's pay-what-you wish fridays from 7pm-10pm, and free with CUNY student ID or if you're under 18.

name: Callen-Lorde Community Health Center
directions: LGBYQ-centric Community health center - just walk in and ask to use it. On the first floor, around the corner, near the pharmacy pick up. Two rooms marked All-Gender Restroom

name: Callen lorde community health center
directions: Multiple floors with bathrooms
comment: This is a safe space for people of all genders, all bathrooms are unisex

name: Starbucks Reserve Roastery

comment: You don’t need to be a paying customer

name: Le pain quotidien

name: American Jewish World Service (AJWS)

comment: Right next to the public restrooms. Labeled as family restroom. Clean and usually empty.

comment: I’d recommend to spend a little time in the library, before you just burst in and use the restroom. It is a unisex, single stall bathroom.

name: Satis Bistro

comment: Paying customers only

name: Starbucks

name: Le Pain Quotidien 53 Street
directions: Back of the restaurant

name: Charlie Palmer Steak

comment: Walk in and tell the host you think you are meeting someone at the bar. Take a look around the bar. Then ask where the restroom is.

name: Larb Ubol, 37th and 9th ave

comment: Best sign ever, saying "anyone can use this restroom regardless of gender identity or expression"
